						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Manta rays can leap completely out of the water. They may do it to escape predators or to communicate with other mantas. The great crashing sound that they make when they re-enter the water can be heard for miles away! They may leap to show fitness during courtship displays, or they may just be playing!
						</text>
